<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99867211283445></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99867211283445><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=15&mid=99867211283445>RE: pets</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=15&mid=99867211283445#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 24th 12:55 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Geeze, sorry bout that everyone.&nbsp;&nbsp;But thinking that mages are weak proves 1) that you're a freaking moron 2) You have never played/grouped with/seen a mage in action have you?  Damn pets, they hit like mad.  Imagine, I am a necro, my pet hits fairly hard, and people in the group (tanks usually) just gape in awe when they see my pet Quad 55.  Then theres the Mages pet.  Hehe, one of my good friend is a mage, wow!  His pet rocks.  Quads for 58 and nukes.  My pet Life Taps, not sure for how much tho.  Necros DD suck, sort of, but none other DD spells are as cool as Ignite/Chill Bones spells(turns mob into a skeleton for those who dont know) but do 600points of dmg max (roughly).  Of course, mages lack the ability to snare/root/fear.  Earth pet roots I think.  But thats a fair trade off for huge AE and DD spells.  Second to the Wiz in DD, mages are great party addition.  My favorites Soloing mates are 1)Mage 2)Druids 3)Shaman.  Mages are very and I mean VERY potent opponents.  Take out their pets and they are pretty much dead, but heck, you have to take out the pet.  Good Luck!<br><br>   The beastmaster will be fun to play.  I think that the best part of EQ is the pet system.  I just love it.  At low level, pet is white/black and yellow.  You just sit down and get exp.  That's nice.  Beastmaster's pet ability to zone is cool.  I dunno if they will do the same to Necros, Mages and all other pet owning classes.  Would be nice.  Bone Chips are hard to come by at higher levels, and newbies know it.  And I don't really want to go hunt skellies for hours just to get a few stacks.<br><br>   All in all, if you think the Beastmaster will be more powerful, then its up to you.  Thrash you char and make a Beastmaster.  Im sure it will be a nice addition to the game, even if it's weak like @#%^.  Enchanters are the best at dying.  Yet, there are many people playing them.  Tanks can't solo worth of @#%^, yet, there are thousands of them out there.  Necros are powerful, VERY powerful, I chose to play a Necro mainly because of the pet.  Well I had to choose between a mage and necro.  Necro won.  So please, stop complaining about one class' weaknesses, no one wants to hear that, especially those who play those classes.  Why not enjoy the game and challenge of playing a much more difficult class?<br><br>I raise my hat to all those Dark Elf Necros(KOS everywhere) Gnomish , Wood Elven and Halfling warriors, Barbarian Rogues and all those humans out there.  Those are the toughest Race/Class combinations to play.  Congratulations to all of you who have made lvl 50+ with such a character.  You rock.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
